# RIASEC / Holland Codes

A career-interest framework developed by psychologist John Holland. Classifies personality into six types — **Realistic, Investigative, Artistic, Social, Enterprising, Conventional** — and matches them to occupational clusters.

## Role in Schola

[[Schola]]'s Career Quiz is built on RIASEC. Students answer situational/preference questions; the output is a "career personality" label (e.g., "Berdarah Seni" = Artistic type) and a ranked list of matched careers.

> [!note] Localisation
> Schola uses Malay-language personality names (e.g., "Berdarah Seni") to make the framework culturally accessible to Malaysian students.

## Why It Matters for Career Guidance

RIASEC provides a psychometrically validated, structured basis for recommending careers — more reliable than informal aspiration surveys. Its use in Schola anchors the [[School-to-Career Transition]] tool in established occupational psychology rather than ad-hoc matching.

